l husbandry, smart city, etc.Graphical programming platformInclusive coding and programming education for children with special needsComplete AI platform for Embedded Machine Learning and IoTThe smallest Arduino-compatible microcontroller in Seeeduino family powered by Microchip SAMD21A series of Single Board Computers for Edge Computing applicationsArduino-compatible kit with 10 Grove sensorsHardware, software, free curriculum, and activities for students to learn about AI, Machine Learning, IoT & Data Science for smart agricultureThe next generation of human-machine interface powered by Raspberry Pi Compute Module 4High-performing, ready-to-use LoRaWAN indoor gateway powered by Helium NetworkCompact and powerful Edge Computing system for various applicationsSelected hardware and software design companies who can support industrial applicationsGraphical programming platform for Embedded Machine Learning\u00a9 2018 \u2013 2021 All rights reserved\u200bPrivacy Policy\u7ca4ICP\u590713058720\u53f7-5", "attributeinfo": {"subpageName": "about-us-2"}}
{"infourl": "https://make.co/", "entity": "make.co", "entitytype": "Competitor", "text": "Get hands-on with kits, books, and more from the Maker ShedOn Maker Campus facilitated by makers but for everyoneMake: Learning Labs for young adultsFind projects for young makersSkill builder, project tutorials, and moreSubscribers' Digital PortalAccess Make: CommunityFind a Maker Faire near youRegister on Maker CampusFind a Makerspace near youStart a local Maker FaireShare a book or article proposalBecome a Make: Community memberHost a class or workshopPost a projectMaker Shed, the official store of Make:From top makers on Maker CampusSubscribe to the premier DIY magazine todayCommunity access, print, and digital Magazine, and moreA juried competition will highlight makers\u2019 creative, technical, and social contributions and their impact worldwide. Learn More\u00a0In this two-day virtual event, get ready to explore maker topics, share ideas, exchange tips and tricks and learn from one another. Learn MoreMaker Camp is a FREE youth program with a focus on using science, technology, engineering, art, and math (STEAM) to create, build, and discover.Geeks1hGeeks\u3067\u306eMaker Faire Bay Area 2014\u30ec\u30dd\u30fc\u30c8\n\u30a2\u30e1\u30ea\u30ab\u306e\u73fe\u5834\u306b\u884c\u3063\u3066\u53d6\u6750\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\u3002\n\u4eca\u5f8c\u30a2\u30e1\u30ea\u30ab\u306e\u30e1\u30a4\u30ab\u30fc\u30ba\u60c5\u5831\u3092\u968f\u6642UP\u3059\u308b\u306e\u3067\u8981\u30c1\u30a7\u30c3\u30af\u3002#geeks #makerfaire\nhttp://geeks-keyofmake.com/articles/12Labos Cr\u00e9atifs3hSalut   \u00e0   la   r\u00e9gion   de   Caraquet!    \n  \n Nous   voulons   souligner   vos   innovations   lors   de   notre   Maker   Faire   scolaire   en   personne   \u00e0   l'\u00c9cole   Marguerite   Bourgeoys   le   19   mai!   Quels   sont   les   projets   cr\u00e9atifs   sur   lesquels   vous   avez   travaill\u00e9s?    \n  \n Inscrivez:   http://bit.ly/3LlqhUP \n  \n...#MakerFaire   Maker Camp6hWe