{"infourl": "https://www.farnell.com/element14/", "entity": "farnell", "entitytype": "Competitor", "text": "Farnell operates as element14 across Asia Pacific. element14 is a high-service distributor of technology products, services and solutions for electronic system design, maintenance and repair.element14 has operations in 10 countries across Asia Pacific and also serve our customers from  Indonesia, Vietnam and Brunei out of Singapore.  We are committed to providing superior customer service with local language websites, local currency, product and shipment needs.   As part of Farnell\u2019s global operations, our access to stock and stronger relationships with suppliers, we are better able to serve your needs.\n                    \n                    Same day despatch, fast delivery\n                    \n                    Easy to access eProcurement tools\n                    \n                    950,000+ products available online\n                    \n                    Excellent customer service\n                    \n                    2,000 leading manufacturers\n                    \n                    FREE technical support", "attributeinfo": {"subpageName": "element14"}}
{"infourl": "https://www.farnell.com/our-heritage/", "entity": "farnell", "entitytype": "Competitor", "text": "Our history started over 80 years ago with two businesses on opposite sides of the Atlantic, each breaking new ground as the radio industry was changing the way the world communicated. The entrepreneurial start-ups known as Farnell in Europe and Newark in North America each began with a simple mission \u2013 help customers get the parts they need, when they need it.The world has changed a lot since the 1930s. The radio engineer has given way to other sorts of engineers: maintenance and facilities engineers, industrial engineers, design engineers, student engineers, and the purchasing professionals who work with them. And what was a simple trade counter and catalogue business has evolved into a global technology company, with over 30,000 products shipped per day.Along the way we have charted our own course, delivering industry first innovations that have defined what is expected of a high-service distributor.Newark Electronics founded.A.C.Farnell Limited founded.First to offer eProcurement capabilities.Premier Farnell plc established following Farnell\u2019s purchase of Premier Electronics, which included the Newark Electronics, MCM and Akron Brass brands.iBuy launched.element14 Community launched; introduced DesignLink and award-winning biodegradable packaging; joined the United Nations Global Compact; acquisition of CadSoft.The Ben Heck Show debuts; achieved Platinum level status in the Business in the Community Index; Asia Pacific region becomes element14.The Knode on element14 launched; listed in the Dow Jones sustainability index; element14 TV debuts.Launch of the Raspberry Pi computer; acquisition of Embest.Acquisition of AVID Technologies.New proposition \u201cThe Development Distributor\u201d launches, displaying how Premier Farnell businesses support customers develop themselves, their products and businesses and the next generation of engineers.Premier Farnell acquired by Avnet Bidco Limited, an indirect, wholly owned subsidiary of Avnet, Inc. and delisted from the London Stock Exchange.Farnell element14 rebranded Farnell, An Avnet Company. Newark element14 rebranded Newark, An Avnet company.  Premier Farnell rebranded Farnell, globally.", "attributeinfo": {"subpageName": "our-heritage"}}
{"infourl": "https://www.farnell.com/products-and-expertise/", "entity": "farnell", "entitytype": "Competitor", "text": "We believe in the power of engineering to deliver innovations that can change the world\u2026as well as those that keep the world running.\n                    One of the broadest lines cards in high service distribution\n                    Our line card includes products, services and solutions that support the design journey, from prototype and test right through to production and maintenance. To keep pace with changing technology, our engineers actively identify and source innovative niche manufacturers for today's most in-demand application areas. Our direct relationships with industry-leading manufacturers, means you can access the very latest technology and information first and as an authorised distributor, we only sell authentic products, so you can be confident you are receiving the highest quality components and services available from proven suppliers\n                    We stock more than 950,000 products and brands from over 2,000 suppliers, 5000 new products added each month, and access to over four million more on demand. We ship more than 19 million order lines every year with the majority of products available for same-day despatch. In addition, our Exclusive Brand portfolio from Multicomp PRO offers reliable components and equipment at low prices, providing you with great value.\n                    Access to engineering expertise to support your needs\n                    We provide access to thousands of engineers through our own support services and our communities to help you bring products to market.\n                    Our Technical Support team of engineers can be contacted online 24/5 for advice on the latest speciality technologies, or alternatively by phone during local normal working hours.\n                    The element14 Community has over 750,000 registered users giving purchasers and engineers access to peers and experts, a wide range of independent technical information and proprietary tools. Users can research a new technology, design an electronic product, or look for parts to repair an existing system. The element14 community also runs road tests, webinars and design challenges for members, as well as providing forum support for products such as Altium CircuitStudio.\n                    ", "attributeinfo": {"subpageName": "products-and-expertise"}}
